<P>- The EverQuest Team </FONT></P></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1989'><br>Gordon Responds</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by Gendarin at 8/16/00 1:57:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1989><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; Times mso-fareast-font-family: ?Times New Roman?; mso-ansi-language: mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA?>Gordon 'Abashi' Wrinn responded today on the Official EverQuest Message Boards. This page will update each time a new response has been made, please click continue to view the preceding ones.</SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE style='MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px'>
<P><U><STRONG><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005277.html'><FONT color=gold>Anti-Twinking</FONT></A><BR></STRONG></U><EM>what the heck! ive worked my butt off to get a high level ( 38 mage ) and now there thinking about turning off twinking in an way, why?<BR>so joe newbie with his leather armor dont feel bad! this is crap ive earned all my stuff and all my other chars stuff and would appreciate not screwing it up. think about it</EM></P>
<P>Our stance on twinking is covered in the FAQ at http://everquest.station.sony.com/forum_faq.html</P>
<P><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005274.html'><FONT color=gold><STRONG>Shaman Group Buffs</STRONG></FONT></A><BR><EM>Why should shamans, the king of buffs, get the worse end of the deal when it comes to group buffs?</EM></P>
<P>It makes sense for single-target buffs to be more effective than group buffs. It's one of the tradeoffs that are in the game. The group buffs have the benefit of affecting a larger number of people with one cast, and therefore less mana, while the single-target buffs have the benefit of being stronger. </P>
<P><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005260.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Najena Revamp</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>There are definitely things happening on the Tarew Marr server. New items are dropping and rubicite (sp) is dropping as well from what i am told.</EM></P>
<P>The revamp of Najena is still planned, but this is not it. This is a bit of a special event.</P>
<P><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005251.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Haste and Delay Rating</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>I was just wondering if it would be technicaly possible to show the delay on a weapon after you have 'haste' spells or itmes on you. I always see people arguing what percentage FBSS has and exe axe ext. </EM></P>
<P>We purposely don't show this information, as it's meant to be derived from experience with the various haste effects. One thing to remember is that items with 'Effect: Haste' do not stack, so only the most potent haste will take effect. Haste spells do, however, stack with haste items.</P>
<P><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005244.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Druid Quest Armor</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>Why is there no quest armor in the game , like warriors crafted, shamans totemic, cleric, sk rouge, pally, ranger, etc.</EM></P>
<P>Check out the last section of the FAQ at <A href='http://everquest.station.sony.com/forum_faq.html.' target=_blank><FONT color=gold>http://everquest.station.sony.com/forum_faq.html</FONT>.</A> It covers the 'why isn't there....' questions fairly well. </P>
<P>In short, there just isn't. There's no mandate anywhere here saying 'There will be no mid-level druid class-specific armor'. There might be quests/armor along those lines some day, just as there might be anything else in the game</P>
<P><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005232.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Quest Camps</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>So, I have to *SIT* and wait 7 hours for the spawn</EM></P>
<P>You aren't required to 'sit and wait' for the NPC. You are only required to be there when the NPC spawns. That can happen at any time, and you could choose to leave and come back later to try and complete the quest. Now, if the item is such that you *choose* to sit and wait, you've made the decision that the item is 'worth it', which is your decision to make. </P>
<P><EM>From what I understand, most quests include a *long* camp to get an item. If you want to control how often the quest is done, just give it more requirements (20+ no drop item list).</EM></P>
<P>More requirements do not limit the amount of items that come into the world. The proliferation of items in the world is tied only to the amount of time it takes to get the rarest item. Even if the quest had 20 one-hour steps, taking you at least 20 hours to complete it, the rate at which items from the quest can come into game is one/hour. The more items that come into the game, the less valuable the items, and the less prestige garnered from acquiring it.</P>
<P><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005206.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Play Nice?</FONT></STRONG></A><BR>I'm not sure why you say that it 'protects' the people taking inappropriate actions. No part of the Play Nice Polices allow that it was that the person was doing. It is, however, true that these things must be witnessed, as we can't allow one person or group of people to adversely affect the account-status of another on word alone. As I'm sure you can imagine, there are people who would use that as an offensive tool if we allowed it. </P>
<P><EM>I turn to my left to see Balorf, running by with his train of literally 50 or more Monsters.</EM></P>
<P>I'd like more information on this if possible. Code was put in a long time ago, before public release of the product, that keeps people from forming a train this long. That many NPCs are not supposed to pursue any one player-character. Once enough NPCs are chasing a player, the others will consider the situation 'well in hand' and go back about thier business.</P>
<P><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005148.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Beta Neutral</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>After speaking to a very nice GM by the name of Valdelmar, I was told that they STILL would not fix it, unless I was a wizard trying to do the Ice Comet quest. I mentioned the posts on here, but he simply said that the Lead GM said he couldn't do it. </EM></P>
<P>I've spoken to the GMs about this, and word will be spread that this faction needs to be reset. I apologize that you've been given the run-around. Please petition again when you get in game.  ...&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?dest=readnews&datakey=1989>continued</a></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1988'><br>Ranger Theme Song</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by Gendarin at 8/16/00 1:52:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1988><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><P>Spotted this over on the offical message boards, a little ballad for rangers by Yendor of Xegony:</P>
