<P>-- The EverQuest Team</P></BLOCKQUOTE></FONT></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1981'><br>New Quest</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by randerson at 8/15/00 6:18:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1981><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lady Daegarmo, Online Events Coordinator&nbsp;for&nbsp;Verant Interactive,&nbsp;made an appearance on the official EverQuest boards about a new tournament that apparently will be taken place across all servers. </SPAN></P>
<P style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><STRONG><SPAN style="COLOR: gold"><A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004737-2.html"><FONT color=gold>The Test</FONT></A></SPAN></STRONG></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><BR>Starting August 27th, the new events launch with the first of the ‘Best of the Best’ series, that will pit the greatest of the servers against the greatest of the servers. During this week all servers will run the Warriors Championship. Rules for this event are simple, with no artifacts, no buffs, and no right clicking on any item (but wearing activatable items is acceptable, just not the use of those items). </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">These events will not have any entry fee, but players must be of 55th level or greater to enter. The winner of the event will be given a title of ‘The Champion’ which is the 51st level title of the class. All of ‘The Champions’ will be copied to Test Server, so that on Sunday at Noon (PST) all of the champions will face each other. Those that place (4th, 3rd, and 2nd places) will receive their 59th level title, and the winner of the ‘Main Event’ will be dubbed the 60th level title (the Warlord).  ...&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?dest=readnews&datakey=1981>continued</a></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1980'><br>Event - Erollisi Marr</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by Gendarin at 8/15/00 4:31:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1980><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><P>This Saturday there will be a Blackburrow raid hosted by The Infinite Realm on the Erollisi Marr server, here is some more information on the event:</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE style='MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px'>
<P>Greetings Young Norrathians! </P>
<P>The Infinite Realm needs your aid! While off adventuring in Kunark it seems that the foul gnolls of Blackburrow have located and raided our warchests and made off with some loot. We ask you to join us in reclaiming these items and ridding Norrath of this scourge on our society. 
<P>On Saturday August 19th beginning at 3 p.m. EST on the Erollisi Marr server the Infinite Realm is happy to host a raid event for young adventurers in Blackburrow and surroundings. 
<P>The gnoll mobs will be equipped with many Fine-Steel weapons and other similar items. Keep what they drop as our reward for your assistance all while under the buffing and healing protection of the Infinite Realm. 
<P>Among the activites:<BR>A Platinum Lottery<BR>Languages Taught<BR>Good-Old Fashioned Killin :)<BR>and throughout the day we will be hosting many mini-quests with prizes such as a Blood-Stained Tunic, Charred Guardian Shield, Class Quest Armor, A full suit of Blackened-Iron, Bronze Armor, Kunark weapons and many many more....</P></BLOCKQUOTE></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1979'><br>Gordon Responds</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by Gendarin at 8/15/00 4:11:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1979><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>Gordon 'Abashi' Wrinn responded today on the Official EverQuest Message Boards. This page will update each time a new response has been made, please click continue to view the preceding ones.</SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE style='MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px'>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><STRONG><U><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005072.html'><FONT color=gold>Mages Spell Drops</FONT></A><BR></U></STRONG>I'm not sure where you've been hunting, or if it's been in a few specific areas, but you might consider trying another areas out. There are some spells, for instance, that don't drop in all areas. If you've been hanging out in a few that have higher spell drops for the other classes, perhaps you've missed any areas that might have higher percentages of mage spells. </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><EM>Now, is this intended, or am I the unluckiest mage in EQ? </EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>That's a possibility as well <IMG src='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/smile.gif'></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005071.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Rubicite in Najena</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>This could be the revamp. You dont know.</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>This is not the revamp. There's some story behind what's happening now, so you might want to look around a bit to see if you can find it. </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005049.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Casual Players</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>In the same 30 hours, a casual player only has about 20 useful hours while a hardcore player has 27. What can be done about it? I don't know. Probably nothing since the game has been out so long.</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>I see your point Twigglin, but what do you propose? It does take time to set up for a group. That time is pretty much the same, regardless of the amount of time that you play in a day. Why is this a penalty? How do you suggest that we 'fix' it? We can't *force* people to take you into a group in 10 minutes, nor can we reduce your travel time (other people have that ability). </P>
<P>Now we are implementing the LFG (Looking for Group) flag. Hopefully this will allow people to determine where a good place to look for a group is, and maybe even arrange the group prior to arriving. This could effectively cut down time 1 &amp; 2, as you know where your going and there's a group there for you. 
<P>I wouldn't say that any of this constitutes a 'penalty' for the casual gamer, but perhaps the person who plays 10 hours per day does indeed get an advantage. I doubt, however, that many groups would stay together for 10 hours without undergoing a period of looking for additional members, which affects them as it does the casual gamer. 
<P>In short, I really don't think that what you are citing is a problem that needs to be 'fixed'.</P>
<P></SPAN><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/005041.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Rallos Looting</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>1. Is there any plans on changing the looting system?</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>No.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><EM>2. Will there ever be a chance to move to another server?</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>Maybe. We're still considering the issue. Nothing is likely to be decided within the next month. I'd really like to see a server-specific polling mechanism put in, but it will be at least two weeks before we can do work on that. It would be at least a week after that before something could go live, and a few more to set up and implement any kind of meaningful poll. That's basically the plan at the moment. Of course it's all subject to change.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><EM>3. Do you have any other options you are working with other then the two mentioned above?</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>Not really. I think that the thoughts posted here have determined without a doubt that there are many different opinions on how PvP should be handled. I don't think that there is a solution that will please everyone, or even most everyone. We're a bit nervous about making any more major changes to the environment going forward.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><EM>My question is WHY HAVE TWO IDENTICAL PVP SERVERS? Would it not make more sense to have:</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>Because there are enough people to support it. More people enjoy playing Teams than they do on an open PvP server like Rallos. Items being allowed, it still makes more sense for it to be allowed on Rallons than on the Teams servers due to the level range.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><EM>BTW, any word on returning pumice stones to merchants as self-only?? </EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>Yes, we've ruled it out as an option, and decided that the current stone is appropriate.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004977.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Impressions of EQ</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>I have see many friends come and go, and made some RL friends because of EQ. With all that has changed over the past 16 months, me included, one thing has remained the same. I love this game. </EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>Thanks Vermy, and everyone else as well. We're always happy to hear from those that are enjoying themselves, and I'm very pleased to see the thread remaining positive <IMG src='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/smile.gif'></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004934.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>High Level Play</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>Or to pay 10,000pp or more. I was told this by a guild today, that at high levels I can not do parts of the game (for which I paid $50 for) unless I join a guild. I feel it is not fair, I do not have 20 or more friends to get to do plane raids, or other high level things.</EM></SPAN></P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>
<P>I'd have to go with DarckHellfire's response. The game is indeed a group game, and the size of a group needed to do certain things goes up as you advance. Most people should have formed relationships by reaching those levels that provide the much needed support. Those who don't form those relationships are usually the ones who solo exclusively or have shown themselves to be a burden to groups through reputation. 
<P>You don't *need* to be in a guild, however guilds are a nice way of making it easier for a large and extended group of friends to recognize each other. It's also useful when it comes to getting some pointers on how to do certain things. Some areas of the game have a bit of a learning curve, and it's sometimes nice to cut off the bottom portion of that curve.</P>
<P></SPAN><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004446.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>CS Complaints</FONT></STRONG></A><BR>It's easy to come here to the boards and assume that something bad is going on behind the scenes because we don't come provide public 'proof' for the account actions we take. We will discuss these issues, but only with the account holder and only via email. We don't drag these issues out to the court of public opinion. </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><EM>BANNINGS should require some solid evidence - they are, after all, permanent. </EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>Bannings do have solid evidence, or we don't do them. It would make sense for us to systematically kick customers off the system, and thus off of our balance sheets, by doing bannings without proof. Please don't assume that just because we won't come here to the boards to 'tell our side' that the proof doesn't exist. </SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><EM>Had they said in that email, 'You've been banned because a senior guide was appointed to monitor your activities. This senior guide watched you make a deal with person_x for 15 fbss's and 15 golden efreeti boots after giving person_x only one of each. Person_x has a reputation for duping items. We've banned you both.' ... or something like that.</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>We won't even give this level of detail to the person banned, let alone state it publicly. I'm sorry, but this is necessary in order for us to conduct business. If we divuldged in detail all of our investigative abilities and powers, we'd open ourselves to those who would search out potential loopholes.&nbsp; ...&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?dest=readnews&datakey=1979>continued</a></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1976'><br>New Comic!</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by randerson at 8/15/00 10:01:00 AM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1976><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: " AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><FONT face=Arial size=2>Woody Hearn, a very talented and accomplished artist brings a fresh face to the EverQuest community with a new comic strip that will be running on a daily basis. The comic strip, /GU..., is also affiliated with both EQanswers.com and the Game Answer Network. Here is the official news release that was sent out:</FONT></SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: " AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><FONT face=Arial size=2>Ready for a </FONT><A href="http://www.gucomics.com/"><FONT face=Arial color=gold size=2><STRONG>DAILY Comic Strip</STRONG></FONT></A><FONT face=Arial size=2> fraught with dazzling color and fast-paced comedic relief? We've got it for you at GUComics.Com. <BR>&nbsp;<BR>The attention getting comic strip 'gu ...' is a single-panel, tongue-in-cheek venture into the world of EverQuest. Not to mention a wonderful addition to your daily line-up of EQ links.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>It's safe to say that you haven't seen anything quite like this in an EQ-based comic, and <BR>we can't offer much more than to say: 'You have to see this for yourself!'.<BR><BR></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Woody Hearn - Cartoonist<BR>'/gu ...' at </FONT><A href="http://www.gucomics.com/"><FONT face=Arial color=gold size=2>GUComics</FONT></A></SPAN></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: " AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: " AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><FONT face=Arial size=2>Thanks Woody, and we hope everyone can check out this hilarious new addition to the EverQuest community.</FONT> </SPAN></P></SPAN></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><font class='header1'>&nbsp;Monday, August 14<hr></font><a class='header2' name='1970'><br>Gordon Responds</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by Gendarin at 8/14/00 6:58:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1970><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>Gordon 'Abashi' Wrinn responded today on the Official EverQuest Message Boards. This page will update each time a new response has been made, please click continue to view the preceding ones.</SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><U><STRONG><A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004822.html"><FONT color=gold>Gordon on the Boards</FONT></A><BR></STRONG></U><EM>spend dozens of hours (hundreds, actually) off-line, discussing, amending and refining your topic over weeks and months, and go to Gordon with proposals you think are the most modest, the most precise, the easiest to implement, and what do you get ? Silence. You are ignored.</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>Nicolbolas, </P>
<P>I'm sorry that I can't address all of your issues, but I can't address *every* issue here on the boards. Besides the fact that there are 300-400 new threads per day, there's another 4000 posts to go with them. This means that chances are your *post* won't be addressed. However, if you stick around long enough, your *issue* probably will. Of course, if your issue has already been addressed, it might be a while before I'll come back to it. There are issues on this board that we could debate full-time for months and never reach any agreeable resolution. I however can't devote all of my time to any one issue. 
<P>You might notice however that I addressed your post on the "Draught" line 20 minutes before you wrote this post. </P>
<P><EM>Is Abashi even around? Why does Verant even pretend this is some kind of company sponsored board?? He has posted like 2 or 3 times in the last week. He gets paid for that?? </EM></P>
<P>Would you all please stop that? I have made posts in no less than 196 threads in the past 10 days, 4 of which were on weekends. That doesn't include multiple posts to the same thread, which are only counted once in the search function. At least have the courteousy to run a search before posting something like this.</P>
<P><EM>Sorry for jumping on you, but I did a search prior to posting that and until a few minutes ago it showed that you hadn't responded to anything since 8-11 on the general discussion boards except maybe 1 or 2 posts. </EM></P>
<P>Today's a bit of a slow (for the boards I mean) day, so I doubt that you'll see much more from me before I take off. Mondays are the meeting days here, sometimes they don't last too long, but today I've been tied up for most of it.</P>
<P><EM>make a board or locked thread with just Abashis Answers and keep it at the top.</EM></P>
<P>There are several websites that are doing that now.</P>
<P></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004807.html"><STRONG><FONT color=gold>GM Events</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>How do I find out more about GM hosted events? I have been playing EQ since release but i always missed those events. Is there anywhere i can find out when is the next event on my server (Mith marr). Thanks </EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>"Events", meaning things like the tests, will soon be posted on the EverQuest.com web page. Quests, however, are another matter, as they are never pre-announced. You'll only be able to find out about them by either being on and involved at the time, or by reading up on them afterwards. We'll soon have quest-stories posted on the official website.</SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004652-2.html"><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Play Nice</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>BTW, this maybe shoulda been on the rants board, but perhaps GW will come down and answer this mere mortal....why why why do you create rules that are detrimental to the players? Play nice started off as a way to prevent KSing and verbal abuse. Play nice should not be exploited as a means of allowing everyone the same chance at a spot in line for toilet paper...err...getting xp. </EM></SPAN></P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>
<P>The Play Nice Policies were created because a growing number of customers were being subordinated by other, more powerful, groups of players. These other groups would claim "ownership" of spawns, loot drops, and even entire zones, refusing to allow other people a chance to experience them. On some servers, guilds had certain areas camped 24x7. 
<P>The play nice policies, in regards to spawns and camping, are designed to promote equal access to the areas. If a group can get into a room, they have as much right to be there as anyone else. Are the policies perfect? No, of course what is? No matter what policy we adopt, there will be people who are helped by the policy, and others that are hurt. Sometimes the policy may help them in one instance and hurt in another. 
<P>As I've mentioned in the past, if anyone has any ideas for policies that are easy to understand, are enforcable, do not require a larger CS team than before or after the Play nice policies, and will please everyone, I'd be happy to discuss them.</P>
<P></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000745.html"><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Wizard Draughts</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>You thought they were small and swift, didn't you ? He he, wrong: </EM></P>
<P><EM>1) Post-50 Wizards don't need the missing large DD spells, because a double cast of Draught does the job (so Draughts are "large" if cast twice...) but<BR>2) Draughts are swift in single-cast, but "slow" in chain-cast, and this might be the hidden reason why some post-50 Wizards feel less effective than before. I suspect Draughts need a cast time of 2.5 instead of 3; </EM></P>
<P>The Draught line was created to give wizards the option of doing less damage at similar mana/damage ratio compared to ice comet, and also to give them similar spells across the three elements that the wizards control. The reasoning behind "less damage" was to reduce the amount that the wizard would aggro the target. Had we wanted to continue along the same lines as ice comet, we could have given similar damage spells with equal damage, mana, and casting time requirements. </P>
<P>In this case, the additional time required to stack two draughts versus one ice comet is what you "pay" for the reduced amount that you aggro the target. </P>
<P></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004665.html"><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Reimbursement for Mistakes</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>According to the Bug board, this spell was a mistake, and should have been labeled as 61 and NOT 16. Ok valid mistake.. However those of us that traded VALUABLE rare drop spells for this are basically being told, tuff luck it's being changed.</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>We're fairly open about the fact that things in game are subject to change at any time. This includes the prospect of both positive and negative changes. People making trades in game need to be aware that that there exists a chance that any item is likely to drop in value or usefulness after you buy it. It's sort of like buying stock in a company in that regard. </P>
<P>The spell was never supposed to be usable by magicians, who ended up able to use it only because the level restriction was transposed by the designer. I really wish we'd caught this sooner.</P>
<P></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004601.html"><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Deleted Post</FONT></STRONG></A><BR>Hello all, I just deleted a post suggesting that a new class ('Witch') be created. The thread was deleted because it degenerated into the disparaging of practiced religion (Wicca). </P>
<P>As a note to the original author of that post, as that certainly wasn't his intention, we wouldn't create a class by that name due to the fact that it does apply to a currently practiced religion. The same doesn't apply to reference to 'priests' or 'monks', as those are nondescript titles in nature, and as such not indicative of any particular religion. </P>
<P></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/003933.html"><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Archery Change</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>There was a hidden nerf in this patch - when you shoot a bow you turn towards the mob you are shooting at. Well, not anymore!!! You now don't turn to face the mob. This allows mobs who run to get out of the line of sight and you miss more.</EM></SPAN></P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: " FONT-SIZE: 12pt; AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times>
<P>Quite frankly this is the first I've seen on the subject. I'll check into it tomorrow. 
<P>-Gordon</P></SPAN></BLOCKQUOTE></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1973'><br>Event - Karana</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by Gendarin at 8/14/00 2:40:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1973><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><P>From Haemish:</P>
