<DIV>Thanks!</DIV></FONT></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1971'><br>Ask Milo</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by Gendarin at 8/14/00 11:12:00 AM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1971><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'>We've updated our <A href='http://www.www.everlore.com/askmilo'><FONT color=gold>Ask Milo column</FONT></A> here at <A href='http://www.everlore.com/'><FONT color=gold>Everlore</FONT></A>, your home for all things EverQuest. This week Milo talks about his love of England, the success of EQ, what kind of character he plays, and a few other topics. It's an interesting and funny read this week, so sit back and enjoy the column. Here's a snip. 
