<P>Still I'm curious what you like about this little place. </P></BLOCKQUOTE></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><font class='header1'>&nbsp;Sunday, August 13<hr></font><a class='header2' name='1969'><br>D&D Movie Spoof</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by randerson at 8/13/00 8:44:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1969><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: " AR-SA? mso-bidi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: mso-ansi-language: Roman?; New ?Times mso-fareast-font-family: Times><FONT face=Arial size=2>Since it is a slow news day, I thought some of our viewers would get a kick out of seeing this, if they haven’t already. If anyone has attempted to play traditional Dungeons and Dragons with a couple of newbies, then this scene can all be too familiar. Check out <A href="http://www.ifilm.com/ifilm/skeletons/film_detail/0,1263,220487,00.html"><STRONG><FONT color=gold>this h<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">ilarious </SPAN>video</FONT></STRONG></A> brought to you by Tim Borrelli who animated the characters from Summoner.</FONT></SPAN></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1968'><br>Gordon Responds</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by randerson at 8/13/00 7:30:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1968><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'><P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: ?Times Times New Roman?; mso-ansi-language: mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA?>Gordon 'Abashi' Wrinn responded today on the Official EverQuest Message Boards. This page will update each time a new response has been made, please click continue to view the preceding ones.</SPAN></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style='MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px'>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: ?Times Times New Roman?; mso-ansi-language: mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA?><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004497.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Banned for INI</FONT></STRONG></A><BR><EM>My question is, does Verant consider this to be a 3rd-party program that can result in banning of players using it?</EM></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: ?Times Times New Roman?; mso-ansi-language: mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA?></SPAN><SPAN style='FONT-FAMILY: ' FONT-SIZE: 12pt; mso-fareast-font-family: ?Times Times New Roman?; mso-ansi-language: mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA?>No, we wouldn't consider use of EQCLIENT.INI editors as cheating. They are just fancy text editors :) I should probably mention that none of them are, however, officially licensed or endorced by Verant/SOE, and that any use of them is at your own risk. Though I'm sure that the vast majority of people would never do this, with the ease of implementing password-stealing code into a 3rd party program, I'd recommend that you be certain of your source. </P>
<P>-Gordon </P></BLOCKQUOTE></SPAN></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><a class='header2' name='1967'><br>Najena Revamp</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by Gendarin at 8/13/00 10:43:00 AM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1967><img src='boards/images/print.gif' alt='Display for Printing' border=0></a><blockquote class='normal'>Reports have been coming in from all servers that the loot tables in the dungeon Nanjena have been changed. Everthing from enchanted fine steel to the once lost Rubicite are now dropping at various places in the dungeon. A few months ago Verant listed Nanjena as one of a few dungeons that they planned on upgrading due to the fact that so few players seem to adventure in them. The others listed were Permafrost and Splitpaw, both seemingly perfect dungeons but ones that are almost never camped to the extent that others are. To talk about this upgrade of Najena and to report any new items or additional changes you can go right <A href="http://www.eqanswers.com/boards/default.asp?dest=allposts&amp;siteid=1001&amp;Forum=ap556501759&amp;ID=40&amp;access=2&amp;status=1&amp;subject=Nanjena+Changes"><FONT color=gold>here</FONT></A>.</blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><div align=right><a href='#top'>to top</a></div><font class='header1'>&nbsp;Saturday, August 12<hr></font><a class='header2' name='1966'><br>Everquest Express #136</a>&nbsp;<font class='small'>by Gendarin at 8/12/00 9:23:00 PM PST</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href='default.asp?dest=profile&action=insert&err=You+must+be+a+registered+user+to+use+answerMail'><img src='boards/images/email.gif' alt='answerMail Author' border=0></a>&nbsp;<a class='news-cont' href=/default.asp?action=print&dest=readnews&datakey=1966><i