<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style='MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px'>
<P><A href='http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004396.html'><STRONG><FONT color=gold>PvP Teams</FONT></STRONG></A><BR>Hello, </P>
<P>I posted this in another thread but it seems to warrant its own. 
<P>The biggest difficulty in regards to PvP in EverQuest is that EverQuest is, and will remain, a primarily PvE (Player versus Environment) game. The addition of PvP to the game should not change the basic fundemental mechanics of EverQuest. PvP in EverQuest has to result in 'EverQuest with PvP' rather than 'PvP EverQuest', if you get my point. 
<P>One of the largest issues on the PvP Teams servers is the subject of cross-teaming. Players of different teams get together for battles. Due to the PvE focus of the game, this has to be allowed for sake of game balance. Though some have suggested that cross-teaming, either in groups or guilds, not be allowed, it's something that will need to remain for the PvE game. 
<P>The problem comes in when cross-teaming is applied to PvP. Cross-teaming creates a situation that is often referred to as the 'invulnarable healer' scenario. Basically, one group of PCs (Team A) attack a group of people on Team B, while supported by a healer from Team B. In this fashion, you have a situation where a member of one team is taking an active role in the deaths of members of their own team. 
